  <text>
    <body>
      <div subtype="original" type="letter" xml:id="L.11935" xml:lang="en">
        <pb facs="#IMG.1" n="1"/>
        <dateline>Llanover<lb/> Abergaveny<lb/>
          <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">South Wales</hi>
          <lb/> Oct 4th 1875<lb/>
          <hi rend="unknown" rendition="#none">Monday</hi>
        </dateline>
        <p> Lady <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2055">
Llanover</persName> presents her compliments to – Professor <persName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.109">Schuchardt</persName>, and having received a letter from her friend Dr Meyer<note
            n="1" place="foot" type="editorial">
            <persName
              ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.persons#P.2187">Kuno Meyer</persName> (1858-1919), Keltologe; vgl. <ref
            target="https://gams.uni-graz.at/context:hsa.letters.2187?locale=de">HSA 07187-07212</ref>.</note>, saying that Professor Schuchardt is now in North Wales &amp;amp; that Lady Llanover might <pb
            facs="#IMG.2"
            n="2"/> be able to be of service in assisting his researches with regard to Ancient languages &amp;amp; Customs of <placeName
            ref="https://gams.uni-graz.at/o:hsa.places#PL.6047">Wales</placeName>. She begs to say, that if Professor Schuchardt visits South Wales she hopes to have the pleasure of seeing him at Llanover where he may possibly find works of interest in <pb
            facs="#IMG.3"
            n="3"/> the Llanover Library. Lady Llanover incloses an Envelope with her address &amp;amp; should she not be at home the letter will be immediately forwarded. Llanover is four Miles from <placeName>

Abergavenny</placeName> &amp;amp; two miles from Hautyderri Station 20 Miles from Brecon &amp;amp; about an hour &amp;amp; a half from <pb
            facs="#IMG.4" n="4"/>

          <placeName>
Cardiff</placeName> – From all of the above places there are Rail roads to Abergavenny or Hautyderry, as well as from <placeName>
Shrewsbury</placeName> through (??) <placeName>
Hereford</placeName>. If Lady Llanover knew of the expected arrival of Professor Schuchardt at Abergavenny or Hautyderri Station she would send a Carriage to meet him.<note
            n="2" place="foot" type="editorial">Der Brief endet hier; möglicherweise fehlt eine Seite.</note>
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
